      "id": "c3d4e5f6-3333-4000-8000-000000000005",
      "name": "Respond Validation Error",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.respondToWebhook",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [960, 440]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## MCP: Airtable Staging Write\n\n**Purpose:** Replace LLM doing data writes to Airtable staging buffer.\n\n**Token savings:** ~4,000 tokens per call\n\n**Flow:** Webhook -> Validate -> IF valid -> Airtable API -> Error Check -> Respond with record ID\n\n**Expected payload:**\n```json\n{\n  \"table\": \"Intake Staging\",\n  \"base_id\": \"appXXXXXXXXXXXXXX\",\n  \"fields\": {\n    \"Name\": \"John Doe\",\n    \"Email\": \"john@example.com\",\n    \"Phone\": \"+14075551234\",\n    \"Case Type\": \"Personal Injury\",\n    \"Source\": \"OpenClaw Chat\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set `AIRTABLE_API_KEY` env var (or better: use n8n HTTP credentials for production)\n2. Update base_id default if using single base\n3. Activate workflow\n\n**Note:** For production, replace the env var Authorization header with a proper n8n HTTP credential. Env vars are for quick testing only.",
        "height": 460,
        "width": 360
      },
      "id": "c3d4e5f6-3333-4000-8000-000000000006",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [240, -180]
    }
  ],
